      "id": "thr_planning_main_product_1",
      "subject": "Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
      "messages": [
        {
          "id": "msg_planning_1_1",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "jordan.johnson@company.com",
            "sam.williams@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
          "body": "Hi Jordan and Sam,\n\nWe need a 45-minute planning session next week to review Main Product progress and agree on next steps for the next sprint.\n\nConstraints:\n- Next week (week of March 3)\n- During working hours Eastern (9a–6p)\n- All of us need to be available\n\nLooking at my calendar, I could potentially do:\n- Tue 3/4: 10:00–10:45, 11:30–12:15, or 15:00–15:45\n- Wed 3/5: 09:30–10:15 or 16:00–16:45\n- Thu 3/6: 11:00–11:45\n\nCan you both reply-all with the slots that work for you, and also flag anything I might be missing on your calendars? Once we converge, I’ll send a calendar invite.\n\nThanks,\nAlex",
          "date": "2025-02-24T10:29:10-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_planning_1_2",
          "from": "jordan.johnson@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com",
            "sam.williams@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
          "body": "Thanks Alex.\n\nLooking at my calendar for next week:\n- Tue 3/4: I’m busy 9:00–10:30 and 11:00–12:00, so 10:00–10:45 and 11:30–12:15 don’t really work. I *can* do 15:00–15:45 on Tue.\n- Wed 3/5: I have Infra Planning 9:00–10:00 and would rather not jump directly into another call, but 09:30–10:15 won’t work anyway. 16:00–16:45 is fine for me.\n- Thu 3/6: I’m out late morning for a doctor’s appointment 10:30–11:30, so 11:00–11:45 doesn’t work.\n\nSo my preferences, in order:\n1) Wed 3/5, 16:00–16:45\n2) Tue 3/4, 15:00–15:45\n\nHappy with either.\n\n– Jordan",
          "date": "2025-02-24T11:02:44-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_planning_1_3",
          "from": "sam.williams@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com",
            "jordan.johnson@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
          "body": "Hey both,\n\nFrom Alex’s options:\n- Tue 3/4: I’m clear until 15:30, but I’d rather not run directly into my 15:30–16:30 code review block. 10:00–10:45 or 11:30–12:15 would be fine. 15:00–15:45 is not great for me since it cuts too close.\n- Wed 3/5: I’ve got standup 9:15–9:45 and an interview block 15:00–17:00. So 09:30–10:15 overlaps standup, but 16:00–16:45 doesn’t work either because I’m interviewing then.\n- Thu 3/6: 11:00–11:45 conflicts with an errand I need to run starting 11:30.\n\nSo for me the best slots are:\n1) Tue 3/4, 10:00–10:45\n2) Tue 3/4, 11:30–12:15\n\nIf neither of those works for everyone, we might have to look at a different day/slot.\n\n– Sam",
          "date": "2025-02-24T11:21:09-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_planning_1_4",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "jordan.johnson@company.com",
            "sam.williams@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
          "body": "Thanks both.\n\nQuick recap of where we are:\n- Jordan can do: Wed 3/5 16:00–16:45 (pref #1), Tue 3/4 15:00–15:45 (pref #2)\n- Sam can do: Tue 3/4 10:00–10:45 or 11:30–12:15, prefers not to run straight into the 15:30–16:30 block\n\nIt looks like there isn’t a clean 45-min overlap in the Tue/Wed windows I initially suggested. I’ll take another pass through our calendars for the week of 3/3 and see if there’s a different 45-min window that works for all three of us.\n\nI’ll follow up in this thread with a concrete proposal once I’ve done a bit more calendar Tetris.\n\nThanks for the quick replies,\nAlex",
          "date": "2025-02-24T11:40:55-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_planning_1_5",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "jordan.johnson@company.com",
            "sam.williams@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
          "body": "Hi again,\n\nI did a broader scan of our calendars for the week of March 3, looking beyond the original times I suggested.\n\nGiven:\n- Jordan’s existing holds (Support/Backend/Infra + doctor’s appointment)\n- Sam’s standups, interview loops, and errand\n- My 1:1s, standups, and other recurring meetings\n\nThe only 45-minute slot that appears open for all three of us, within 9:00–18:00 ET and without butting right up against other meetings for more than one person, is:\n\n- Thu 3/6, 13:00–13:45 ET\n\nIt’s a bit outside our initial Tue/Wed focus, but it fits the constraints and keeps us from stacking back-to-back calls too aggressively.\n\nCan you both double-check and confirm that Thu 3/6, 13:00–13:45 ET works on your side? If so, I’ll send a calendar invite titled “Main Product – Sprint Planning / Next Steps” with a short agenda (current sprint status, blockers/dependencies, next sprint scope, and owners for follow-ups).\n\nBest,\nAlex",
          "date": "2025-02-24T12:15:55-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_planning_1_6",
          "from": "jordan.johnson@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com",
            "sam.williams@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
          "body": "Thu 3/6, 13:00–13:45 ET works for me.\n\nThanks for doing the calendar Tetris.\n\n– Jordan",
          "date": "2025-02-24T12:24:03-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_planning_1_7",
          "from": "sam.williams@company.com",
          "to": [
            "alex.smith@company.com",
            "jordan.johnson@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
          "body": "Works for me as well. 13:00–13:45 ET on Thu 3/6 is free on my side.\n\n– Sam",
          "date": "2025-02-24T12:28:47-05:00"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_planning_1_8",
          "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
          "to": [
            "jordan.johnson@company.com",
            "sam.williams@company.com"
          ],
          "subject": "Re: Planning session for Main Product – find a 45-min slot next week",
          "body": "Perfect, thanks for confirming.\n\nI’ve just sent a calendar invite for:\n- \"Main Product – Sprint Planning / Next Steps\"\n- Thu 3/6, 13:00–13:45 ET\n- Zoom link in the invite\n\nTentative agenda:\n1) Review current sprint status\n2) Identify blockers and dependencies\n3) Align on scope for the next sprint\n4) Assign owners and due dates for follow-ups\n\nIf there’s anything specific you’d like to add to the agenda, feel free to reply here and I’ll update the calendar description.\n\nThanks,\nAlex",
          "date": "2025-02-24T12:40:45-05:00"
        }
      ]
    },
